# Sumiya, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Sumiya (; Dargwa: Сумиямахьи) is a rural locality (a selo) in Duakarsky Selsoviet, Dakhadayevsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 149 as of 2010.
Geography
Sumiya is located 36&nbsp;km southwest of Urkarakh (the district's administrative centre) by road. Duakar and Karbuchimakhi are the nearest rural localities.
